<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-30T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-30T15:00:00-05:00" n="393" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d393">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">759.6214/62: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Colonel <persName type="to">E. M. House</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-30T15:00:00-05:00">November 30, 1918—3 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>101. Department has received following telegram from Copenhagen: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“3186, November 24, 2 p.m. My 3155, 18th.<note n="1" xml:id="d393fn1">See Department’s telegram No. 55, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Politiken</hi> reported yesterday that
                                    Hanssen-Nørremølle arrived Berlin last Friday, and handed to
                                    Danish Minister statement to be sent Danish Government wherein
                                    Danish population North Schleswig ask Denmark to accept Danish
                                    portion of that province. Government are further requested to
                                    take up North-Schleswig question at Peace Conference.
                                    Grant-Smith.”</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>